QR- Decomposition 
- Decomposition of matrix A 
- A = Q * R
- Split matrix into orthogonal (Q) and upper triangular factors (R)
- Q is a square and orthogonal such that its transpose is its inverse 
- Q R function in Julia
- Focus on symmetric arrays A 
- A(k) = Q(k) * R(k)
    - A (k+1) = Q(k, Transpose) * A(k) *Q(k)
- If || A(k+1) - A(k)|| ≤ E ; set converge to true and return eigenvalues ---> where || A(k+1) - A(k)|| = 1 is the matrix norm
- QR iteration gives eigenvalues along main diagonal 
